name: 3.6 The Chook Sparkling Shiraz, Australia $24
notes:
- leave skin on for a long time, dark grape variety
- red wine made in barrels first and then moved to tanks -> adds more sugar and yeast (second fermentation)

name: 3.5 Bertani Amarone Valpantena, Italy $72
notes:
- collects grapes with higher sugar in preproduction, then dry the grapes to get higher in sugar
- expensive because low on juice
ripasso - will be similar to this dried flavor while still holds the lightness of "Buglioni Valpolicella Classico"

name: 3.4 Buglioni Valpolicella Classico, Italy $22
notes:
- not in a barrel
- skin spent less time

name: 3.3 Monemvasia Kydonitsa Mature, Greece $26
notes:
- complex wine, a lot of flavors and smells
- amber wine
- 10 hours of skin contact that brings astringency
- 3 years in a bottle (aging makes it less fruity)
- skin contact white (leaving skins on for fermentations)

name: 3.2 Rodica Malvadiesel, Slovenia $20
notes:
Nature wine has yeast but also bacteria, yeast leaves the last.
Oxidative wine through natural process, bacterias adds odors the same way in beers.
(wines usually don't have bacterias, they get killed before fermentation)
Unfiltered wine adds texture, less stirring makes it heavy.
8 hours of skin contact - orange wine.

name: 3.1 Domaine de la Hersandiere Muscadet Sevre-et-Maine, France $22
notes:
- acid-driven wine, not so fruit, yeasty
Less stirring leaves yeast with the wine and adds weight to the texture

name: 2.7 La Rioja Alta Vina Alberdi Rioja Reserva, Spain $25
notes:
- 1st year new American barrels + 2nd year old barrel
- pair with smoked meat like lamb

name: 2.6 Gorgo Bardolino, Italy $18
notes:
- fruit-forward, has ashy smoky, fruit wine
Full body means it's heavy and high in alcohol.

name: 2.5 Torbreck Juvenile Red, Barossa, Australia $25
notes: - left the skin on to get tanin then remove some skin

name: 2.4 Le Fraghe Chiaretto, Bardolino, Italy $16
notes:
- left the skin in for as long as before fermentation
- crush the grapes, leave the skins on for 4h to 4 days until the color is right

name: 2.3 Di Lenardo Gossip Pinot Grigio, Friuli, Italy $15
2.2 Livio Felluga Pinot Grigio, Friuli, Italy $32
1.6 Francesco Montagna Moscato, Lombardy, Italy $15
notes: Sweetness remains when the winemaker intervene to stop the yeast from breaking down the sugar. Like cold temperature... Sourness is hard to tell when it is sweet.

name: 2.1 Tushpa Pet Nat Lalvari, Armenia $25
notes: Ancient method: poured into a bottle & continued fermentation in bottles, yeast because it's trapped (no second fermentation), no cork because it eventually will have enough pressure to push it out but not enough that they need a champagne cork.

1.1 Mer Soleil Silver Unoaked Chardonnay, Monterrey, CA $16
notes: This is unoaked wine, fermented in steel tank. Astringency rarely comes with white wines because it usually comes from the skins of grapes.
